Brazil is a large complex country that is undergoing rapid economic, social, and 
environmental change. In this Series of six articles, we have reported important 
improvements in health status and life expectancy, which can be ascribed largely 
to progress in social determinants of health and to implementation of a 
comprehensive national health system with strong social participation. Many 
challenges remain, however. Socioeconomic and regional disparities are still 
